{"word":"στένω","slug":"στένω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>στένω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and impf \n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to moan, sigh, groan</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>to moan</i> or <i>sigh for</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>ὑπέρ τινος</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>τινί</el> or <el>ἐπί τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn., <el>πένθος οἰκεῖον στ.</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to bewail, lament</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>στένειν τινὰ τῆς τύχης</el> <i>to pity</i> him <i>for</i> his ill fortune, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>: so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <el>στένεσθαί τινα</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}